<paragraph blockId="12.[192,1440,812,900]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,278,812,836]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Notes.</emphasis>
The presence of pale yellowish-brown pubescence on the mesosoma will separate females of this species from the other Amazon basin species of subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[922,1089,844,868]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Schonnherria">
<emphasis box="[922,1089,844,868]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Schonnherria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which generally have dark brownish-black to black mesosomal pubescence.
</paragraph>
